title: For Sale:  A Rare Pair of Billinghurst Rifles
postcontent: J.J. Miller of Syracuse was the first to patent a multi shot cylinder, in about 1840, long before Samuel Colt used the cylinder in his guns.  Billinghurst was his gunsmith.  After Miller died, Billinghurst started his own company using Miller's patent.  The cylinder gun you see in the photo is a Billinghurst 40 caliber, made in about 1850, by the Billinghurst Company.  The 40 caliber single shot plains rifle, is a J.J. Miller, approximate 1843.  When you hold the guns side by side, you can tell they are made by the same gunsmith.  The detail and the finish have many similarities.  Call or email and I will send more photos.

title: For Sale:  Nickel Boron AR15 Bolt Carrier Group
postcontent:
At BicKen Plating, we don't just provide a service for the gun enthusiast, we plate our own gun parts and are gun enthusiasts ourselves. Using our own equipment to perfect our techniques, we live by the quality product we offer by using it in our own firearms. We offer something that is made for and produced by the serious shooter.

Nickel Boron has been receiving a lot of positive attention in the firearms community for many reasons. Firstly, it provides your guns parts with a finish that is highly resistant to corrosion. You will no longer have to worry about moisture causing rust on your firearm parts. It is also very resistant to wear, which is extremely important when working with parts that are constantly in motion. Lastly, Nickel Boron plating is self lubricating. You no longer have to worry about adding excessive amounts of oil which collects carbon residue and debris which can cause your firearm to malfunction. This cuts down on maintenance and cleaning requirements.

---------------------------------

For your consideration is a full auto AR-15 Bolt Carrier Group that has been plated in Nickle Boron.  This is a new BCG that has never been installed in an upper reciever.

For more information on Nickel Boron, or how to get your parts plated, contact us via email.

title: For Sale:  Colt LE-6940 AR15 RESTRICTED Rollmark - AR-15 NIB
postcontent:
Colt is commonly regarded as producing the best AR-15s and the LE 6940 is their top of the line model. It uses a monolithic upper which is machined from a large single aluminum block instead of most AR15s which have extruded rails bolted on.

The advantages are: Improved accuracy - the rails don't contact the barrel throwing off accuracy. Also because the rail is continuous, you don't have to use cantilevered mounts when mounting long scopes, making for a more rigid optics platform. Also when mounting lasers, they stay truer to the bore axis. A more rigid platform with fewer parts to break, work loose, or lose. 

In addition to being the top of the line commercially made AR15, this is the most desirable LE6940 in terms of collectibility. Colt introduced the LE6940 with the "RESTRICTED MILITARY / GOVERNMENT LAW ENFORCEMENT / EXPORT USE ONLY" rollmark on the right side. It was of course perfectly legal for consumers to own but was marked the same as their military M4s. Then they changed to the "Sporter" SP6940s without the rollmarks, which caused an uproar among collectors who hated the "Sporter" markings. In response Colt then changed the designation back to LE6940 but the "RESTRICTED..." rollmark was never brought back. This is a rare LE6940 with the "RESTRICTED" rollmark and it is 100% NEW IN BOX. It has never been fired or even had a magazine inserted into it. 

This is as pristine of an original LE6940 as you will find. Comes COMPLETE with all original accessories including: Flip up rear and front sights Original box Instructions Bag which contained: Two 20rd mags (that's how colt shipped them). Original plastic bag for the rifle. Must be legal to purchase
